track_notes:
2.2 mile hike along the Bartram Trail with 1100 of EG.  Parking for several vehicles is available at 34.872, -83.295, where the Bartram Trail crosses Pool Creek Road.  At approximately 1.75 miles, I left the Bartram Trail and followed the NE ridgeline to the summit.  Once on top, it was easy to see that there was indeed a well-established trail heading down the NW ridgeline back to the Bartram Trail.  I estimate that route would add around another half mile to the hike.

Summit is typical southern hardwoods, with decent space for setting up.
track_title: W4G/NG-058 Rainy Mtn via Bartram Trail Northbound

track_notes: This route avoids the off-trail portion up the northeast ridgeline of Rainy Mtn and continues around to the official summit trail on the western ridgeline. This route is 1.25 miles longer than my other route with a considerable bit more elevation loss and gain. Considering how nice the off-trail hike is on the other route, I would not recommend this route if hiking northbound on the Bartram Trail. But, his may be the better option in the summertime.
track_title: W4G/NG-058 - Rainy Mtn via Bartram Trail and Summit Trail
